wikipedia_page.main: Colonel Walter Tremenheere  (10 September 1761 – 7 August 1855) was a senior officer in the Royal Marines. He was born at Penzance on 10 September 1761, and is buried at Kensal Green Cemetery, London.His eldest son, Colonel Hugh Seymour Tremenheere (1804–1893), was a publicist and author.
